<li>Wisnioski, Matthew. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sciencemag.org/content/332/6037/1504.summary">"Let's Be Fysiksists Again"</a>, <i>Science</i>, vol 332, issue 6037, 24 June 2011, pp.&#160;1504–1505.</li>
</ul>
<dl>
<dt>Books</dt>
</dl>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Fritjof_Capra" title="Fritjof Capra">Fritjof Capra</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Tao_of_Physics" title="The Tao of Physics">The Tao of Physics: An Exploration of the Parallels Between Modern Physics and Eastern Mysticism</a>. Shambhala Publications, 1975.</i></li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Amit_Goswami_(Physicist)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Amit Goswami (Physicist) (page does not exist)">Amit Goswami</a>. <i>The Self-Aware Universe</i>. Tarcher, 1995.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jack_Sarfatti" title="Jack Sarfatti">Jack Sarfatti</a>. <i>Space-Time and Beyond</i>, with <a href="/wiki/Fred_Alan_Wolf" title="Fred Alan Wolf">Fred Alan Wolf</a> and Bob Toben, E. P. Dutton, 1975.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Evan_Harris_Walker" title="Evan Harris Walker">Evan Harris Walker</a>. <i>The Physics of Consciousness: The Quantum Mind and the Meaning of Life</i>. Da Capo Press, 2000.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Ken_Wilber" title="Ken Wilber">Ken Wilber</a> (ed). <i>Quantum Questions: Mystical Writings of the World's Great Physicists</i>. Shambhala Publications, 2001 (first published 1984).</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Gary_Zukav" title="Gary Zukav">Gary Zukav</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Dancing_Wu_Li_Masters" title="The Dancing Wu Li Masters">The Dancing Wu Li Masters</a></i>. HarperOne, 2001 (first published 1979).</li>
</ul>


